id: pm-todos-ejm7
title: Preserve rich JSONL fields across installed pm-todos import/export
description: "Greptile reproduced that JSONL parsing retained rich fields but runTodoImport dropped them before pm persistence, causing export-after-import data loss."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: data-fidelity,jsonl,review-finding,sdk
created_at: "2026-07-10T23:20:58.173Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-11T00:52:49.930Z"
deadline: "2026-07-11T23:20:58.173Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-10T23:21:52.657Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "A real installed pm-todos package imports and exports id, title, description, status, type, priority, tags, deadline, assignee, sprint, source timestamps, todo dates, and kv without loss; object kv values normalize to JSON strings; package doctor reports zero warnings; unit and release gates pass."
definition_of_ready: PR #22 is checked out and Greptile/CodeRabbit findings are available.
reviewer: greptile
risk: medium
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-07-production
release: next
reporter: codex
severity: high
environment: "pm CLI 2026.7.10, Node 22.19.0"
repro_steps: Install the branch into an isolated tracker; import JSONL containing object kv and rich metadata; export JSONL; compare all public fields.
resolution: "Preserved rich JSONL fields through declared SDK fields, made sync inputs fully declared, rejected empty filter values, and added a default no-empty-overwrite guard with explicit --allow-empty acknowledgement."
expected_result: Installed-package JSONL import/export preserves all 15 supported public fields without mutating pm-owned audit metadata.
actual_result: 120 tests plus installed-package JSONL import/export/sync pass; real --file sync works; restrictive-filter sync returns a USAGE error and preserves the source bytes; production audit is clean; package/changelog gates pass; no dist artifacts remain tracked.
affected_version: 2026.7.10
fixed_version: next
component: index.ts
regression: true
customer_impact: "Agents lose task context during backup, migration, or synchronization."
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-todos-gcjm,related,"2026-07-10T23:20:58.173Z",codex,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T23:20:58.173Z",codex,Greptile review on PR #22 identified the persistence gap; CodeRabbit tracker findings were remediated in the same feedback round.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T23:20:58.173Z",codex,Reserved pm audit fields must remain authoritative; source timestamps are preserved in namespaced SDK fields and projected back only at JSONL export.
learnings[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T23:20:58.173Z",codex,"Parser-level round-trip tests are insufficient for importers: persistence and re-export must be tested through a real installed package."
  "2026-07-11T00:40:35.374Z",codex,Bidirectional sync must treat a zero-row export as potentially destructive context loss; require explicit acknowledgement before replacing a non-empty source file.
  "2026-07-11T00:52:49.929Z",codex,"Review hardening: treat blank JSONL source-date metadata as absent before constructing --field arguments, preventing malformed empty date values from reaching the core CLI."
